
[1]hyperborean

   HYPERBO'REAN, a. [L. hyperboreus; Gr. beyond, and the north.]

   1. Northern; belonging to or inhabiting a region very far north; most
   northern.

   2. Very cold; frigid.

      HYPERBO'REAN, n. An inhabitant of the most northern region of the
   earth. The ancients gave this denomination to the people and places to
    the northward of the Scythians, people and regions of which they had
    little or no knowledge. The Hyperboreans then are the Laplanders,the
               Samoiedes, and the Russians near the White Sea.
